SIMPLE: globulimeter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Globulimeter
<hw>Glob`u*lim"e*ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Globule</ets> + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>An instrument for measuring the number of red
blood corpuscles in the blood.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The method depends on the differences of tint obtained
by mixing a sample of the blood with sodium carbonate
solution.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Globulin</ent>⟦br⟧
